  "response": "Yes, money laundering falls under criminal legislation in most countries. It is typically considered a serious financial crime that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, making it appear to have come from a legitimate source. Money laundering is usually prosecuted under criminal law and can result in significant legal penalties, including:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n2. Substantial fines\n3. Imprisonment\n4. Asset seizure\n\nMany countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations that criminalize such activities and require financial institutions to report suspicious transactions.",
